README for fzf


OVERLAY NOTES

fzf is written in Go, which defaults to GOARM=7 (assumes VFPv3) when
GOARM isn't set explicitly. This board's CPU is an ARM1136/VFP11 core
(ARMv6, VFPv1/VFPv2 only, no VFPv3) — a GOARM=7 binary crashes with
SIGILL on startup here.
 
This overlay adds `GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm GOARM=6` before the `go build`
step to match this CPU. Any other Go-based port on this board needs the
same fix, since Go gives no build-time warning for the mismatch — the
binary just crashes at runtime.
